CNCP v1 23106
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#13228: Attributes with `undefined` value are not removed",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:20:59.532020+00:00",
  "text": "Attributes with `undefined` value are not removed\n\n### Vue version\n\n5.8.3\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\n[Playground](https://play.vuejs.org/#__SSR__)\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```vue\n<script lang=\"ts\" setup>\nimport { ref } from 'vue'\n\nconst msg = ref('Hello World!')\n</script>\n\n<template>\n  <h1 :style=\"undefined\" :class=\"undefined\">{{ msg }}</h1>\n  <input v-model=\"msg\" />\n</template>\n```\n\nWhen SSR is **OFF** it renders `<h1 class>...</h1>`.\nWhen SSR is **ON** it renders `<h1 style class>...</h1>`.\n\n### What is expected?\n\nWhen attribute has `undefined` value it should be completely removed from node: `<h1>...</h1>`\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nAttribute names are present but with empty values.",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
